    "text": "That revved feeling is your nervous system still in workout mode — a hard evening session keeps heart rate and temperature elevated at bedtime, and it fading as you wind down is normal, whereas a pounding or irregular heartbeat on nights you haven't trained would be worth a medical look. Your sleep itself is holding up well: 7.4 hours last night, matching your 7.4 h weekly average, with recovery at 63% and HRV of 68 ms above your 65.4 baseline. Yesterday's session was genuinely big — a 19.5 load over 77 minutes — so the fix is buffer, not less training: finish hard sessions earlier in the evening when you can, and when you can't, insert a deliberate wind-down of a cool shower, dim light, and no screens between the last set and bed. Your ring will show the fall-asleep time improving.",
